Rescue mission successful! This beautiful peacock was hit by a car and the driver just kept going...! The poor guy was left in the road, alive but just not able to move, rush of traffic thankfully at least driving to avoid hitting him again. My son and I were able to wrap him in some blankets and get him to the wonderful folks (David and Eric) at Sacred Lands Preservation and Discover Florida Tours who will take care of him until the Birds in Helping Hands team arrives.  So thankful for caring people like these!
This beautiful peacock was so calm through it all and we’re praying he will make a full recovery! 🙏 🦚 
#peacock #sobeautiful #jungleprada #weliveonaplanet and we #share it with other #awesome #creatures #thankful #peacockinatesla

Wow! So great to see her again!
